It’s a new joint at rea farms. Whenever I crossed it, saw a bunch of people enjoying the delicacies there. Friday evening we went to try it out. The place was crowded and busy but the overall store was very neat and had good options
It has more desserts and less savory ones.
Overall a good experience . Will go again
Excellent coffee! Excellent pastry! The people who work there are very nice, but service is sloooow. The atmosphere is bright and clean. Lovely esthetic.

Finally - good bread!   Their pastries are beautiful and will definitely be trying
Some in the future.     Can’t wait for Indian Land to open.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words, Deb! We're delighted to hear you enjoyed our bread and look forward to you trying our pastries. We can't wait to welcome you to our Indian Land location!

reviews_data.review_text: This place has a great vibe and I really love the overall concept. My only concern is around cleanliness—I’ve noticed some customers touching their hair and then reaching directly into the pastry case, which raises some sanitary concerns. Personally, I’d feel more comfortable if the staff handled and served the pastries. Just something I observed. Otherwise, it’s a very nice spot!

reviews_data.review_text: Came here on Sunday at 7pm- they close at 9. They were out of everything. This was an hour drive.

reviews_data.review_text: I have been to this place 2-3 times and I love the concept. Pastries are amazing and at a reasonable price. Considering they have been only open for 1 week I feel they are doing amazing, it takes a while for new staff to get trained and somehow all these new employees managed to do the job with a smile on their face and efficiently. I was there today in the morning and people didn’t stop coming in as stressful as it must be to deal with so many customers and being trained at the same time, the person that helped me at the registered was very polite and attentive. I love the fact that they open early and close late.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words, Claudia! We're delighted to hear you love our concept, pastries, and appreciate our staff's dedication. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: We’ve been waiting since last year for this place to open, and today we finally got to try it — every bite of the pastry was absolutely delicious. So worth the wait!Thanks so much 🌹.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words, Moha! We're delighted to hear that our pastries were worth the wait and that you enjoyed every bite. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
We came on a Saturday morning for breakfast at 8 am. Shelves were almost empty with just a few pastries and no breakfast sandwiches available. We waited for around 20 minutes to get a breakfast croissant that was unremarkable and we had to eat them from the tray( no plates provided). The layout is a mess as lines get crowded when the staff tries to replenish the shelves. The staff is quite disorganized. You see a lot of people working while a lot of people are waiting.
The ambiance is very nice, well decorated and welcoming. I will give it a second chance in a couple of more weeks and see if they can get more organized.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback, Monica. We're sorry to hear about your experience with the breakfast selection and service. Please share your concerns at contactus@parisbaguette.com, citing your review.

reviews_data.review_text:
Been waiting for Paris Baguette in Charlotte, ever since we moved out from NJ/NY. We finally have one in Charlotte area!
As always, all sweet/savory items here taste good and are rich in quality.
We had to try Tous les jours a couple of times, since we did not have Paris Baguette in Charlotte. Tous les jours always felt like a cheap copy of Paris Baguette, with almost same or higher prices than PB.
This PB location is a must visit, it has a good vibe to it.

reviews_data.review_text:
This area needed a good cafe, so finally! Coffee and croissants, what can be better? The variety is huge, there’s a ton of different types of pastries, sweet or savory. We tried one of different kinds. We were not fans of buns with sausages, those tasted rather regular, rice cake made my daughter stomach ache, Palmiers are way too sugary. Classic croissants were my favorite and we loved the crab “cakes”.
Baguettes are 3$ a piece and are a bit too thick to my taste.
Hazelnut coffee is good. But no matter the preference you can always find something for yourself here, and we are still in the discovery process. We are overjoyed that we have a nice coffee place here! Thanks a bunch!
